RAILS CONCEPT: This is an ERB (Embedded Ruby) template that combines HTML with Ruby code.
ERB allows us to insert dynamic content into HTML using special tags:
- <% %> executes Ruby code but doesn't output anything
- <%= %> executes Ruby code AND outputs the result to the HTML
- <%# %> creates comments that won't appear in the final HTML

FILE NAMING CONVENTION: Rails automatically looks for this file when the 
HomeController's index action completes. The pattern is:
app/views/[controller_name]/[action_name].html.erb

LAYOUT INHERITANCE: This view will be inserted into the application layout
(app/views/layouts/application.html.erb) where the <%= yield %> tag appears.
